message.reasoning_content:
The user is asking me to respond to a survey about AI in education. I need to provide responses for all 10 statements about AI. I'm role-playing as a primary or secondary school teacher from the Republic of North Macedonia.

Let me think about reasonable responses for each statement from a teacher's perspective:

[TT4G35A]: "Artificial intelligence helps teachers write or improve lesson plans." - This is generally true. AI can assist with lesson planning. I would agree with this.

[TT4G35B]: "Artificial intelligence enables teachers to adapt learning material to different students' abilities." - This is also true. AI can personalize content. I would agree with this.

[TT4G35C]: "Artificial intelligence assists teachers in supporting students individually." - Yes, AI can help with personalized support. I would agree with this.

[TT4G35D]: "Artificial intelligence supports students with specific needs (e.g. multilingual learners, students with special education needs)." - This is true. AI has capabilities in this area. I would agree with this.

[TT4G35E]: "Artificial intelligence helps teachers automate administrative tasks." - Yes, definitely. I would agree with this.

[TT4G35F]: "Artificial intelligence enables students to misrepresent others' work as their own." - This is a concern/risk with AI. I would agree that this is a problem.

[TT4G35G]: "Artificial intelligence makes recommendations that may not be appropriate or correct." - Yes, this is a real concern. AI can make mistakes. I would agree with this.

[TT4G35H]: "Artificial intelligence amplifies biases that reinforce students' misconceptions." - This is also a legitimate concern about AI. I would agree with this.

[TT4G35I]: "Artificial intelligence jeopardises the privacy and security of student data." - This is a valid concern. I would agree with this.

[TT4G35J]: "Artificial intelligence suggests unsuitable pedagogical approaches that teachers would use with students." - This could happen. I would agree with this concern.


A teacher would recognize both the genuine benefits AI offers—from streamlining lesson planning to personalizing instruction for diverse learners—and the legitimate risks it poses, including data privacy concerns, potential biases, and the possibility of students using it to plagiarize. My responses reflect this balanced perspective across all ten statements.
